---

# Coding Conventions

## 1. General Principles

### 1.1 Code Must Be

Code phải đảm bảo:

| Principle                        | Meaning                             |
| -------------------------------- | ----------------------------------- |
| **Readable**                     | Code phải dễ đọc hơn là clever      |
| **Explicit**                     | Tránh magic behavior                |
| **Consistent**                   | Naming và structure phải thống nhất |
| **Domain-driven**                | Business logic nằm trong domain     |
| **Framework-independent domain** | Domain không phụ thuộc Spring       |

---

# 2. Naming Conventions

## 2.1 Class Naming

| Type            | Convention                | Example                 |
| --------------- | ------------------------- | ----------------------- |
| Entity          | `<Entity>`                | `Account`               |
| Repository      | `<Entity>Repository`      | `AccountRepository`     |
| Jdbc Entity     | `<Entity>JdbcEntity`      | `AccountJdbcEntity`     |
| Jdbc Repository | `<Entity>JdbcRepository`  | `AccountJdbcRepository` |
| Use Case        | `<Action><Entity>UseCase` | `CreateAccountUseCase`  |
| DTO             | `<UseCase><Type>`         | `CreateAccountRequest`  |
| Controller      | `<Entity>Resource`        | `AccountResource`       |
| API Interface   | `<Entity>Api`             | `AccountApi`            |
| Enum            | `<Entity>Status`          | `AccountStatus`         |
| Error Enum      | `<Entity>Error`           | `AccountError`          |

---

## 2.2 Method Naming

### Use Case

```java
execute(...)
executeCreate(...)
executeActivate(...)
```

Example

```java
createAccountUseCase.execute(request)
```

---

### Repository Queries

| Pattern          | Example           |
| ---------------- | ----------------- |
| existsBy<Field>  | `existsByEmail`   |
| findBy<Field>    | `findByEmail`     |
| findAllBy<Field> | `findAllByStatus` |
| countBy<Field>   | `countByStatus`   |

---

### Domain Behavior

Entity methods nên mang ý nghĩa **business action**.

Good:

```java
activate()
suspend()
changeEmail()
resetPassword()
```

Bad:

```java
setStatus()
setEmail()
```

---

# 3. Package Naming

Package phải dùng **lowercase**.

Structure:

```
dev.ngb.<module>.<context>.<layer>
```

Example:

```
dev.ngb.app.iam.web
dev.ngb.app.iam.application
dev.ngb.core.domain.iam
dev.ngb.core.database.jdbc.iam
```

---

# 4. Entity Conventions

## 4.1 Entity Design Rules

Entity phải:

* không public constructor
* có factory method
* chứa business behavior
* không expose setters

Example:

```java
@Getter
public class Account extends DomainEntity<Long> {

    private Account() {}

}
```

---

## 4.2 Factory Method Naming

Factory methods phải dùng:

```
create()
reconstruct()
```

Example

```java
Account.create(email)
```

---

## 4.3 Domain Behavior

Domain logic phải nằm trong entity.

Example:

```java
account.activate()
```

Không làm:

```java
accountService.activate(account)
```

---

## 4.4 Entity Fields

Order field theo thứ tự:

```
id
uuid
audit fields
business fields
relations
```

Example:

```java
id
uuid
createdAt
updatedAt

email
status
```

---

# 5. Repository Conventions

## 5.1 Repository Interface

Repository interface **chỉ định nghĩa contract**.

Example:

```java
public interface AccountRepository extends Repository<Account, Long>
```

---

## 5.2 Repository Implementation

Repository implementation:

```
AccountJdbcRepository
```

Location:

```
core/database/jdbc/<context>/repository
```

---

## 5.3 Query Strategy

Prefer:

```
existsBy(field)
findOneBy(field)
```

Avoid writing raw SQL nếu không cần.

Use SQL only when:

* complex join
* performance optimization

---

# 6. Use Case Conventions

## 6.1 One Use Case = One Business Action

Good:

```
CreateAccountUseCase
ActivateAccountUseCase
SuspendAccountUseCase
```

Bad:

```
AccountService
AccountManager
AccountHandler
```

---

## 6.2 Use Case Structure

Use case class:

```java
@RequiredArgsConstructor
public class CreateAccountUseCase implements UseCaseService
```

---

## 6.3 Use Case Method

Use case method:

```
execute(...)
```

Example

```java
public void execute(CreateAccountRequest request)
```

---

## 6.4 Use Case Responsibilities

Use case phải:

1. validate conditions
2. load entities
3. call domain behavior
4. persist changes

Use case **không nên chứa logic phức tạp**.

---

# 7. DTO Conventions

## 7.1 DTO Type

Use Java `record`.

Example:

```java
public record CreateAccountRequest(
        String email,
        String password
) {}
```

---

## 7.2 DTO Scope

DTO phải **scoped per use case**.

Structure:

```
usecase/<feature-group>/<usecase>/dto
```

Example:

```
registration/register_account/dto/RegisterAccountRequest
```

---

## 7.3 DTO Rules

DTO:

| Rule              | Reason                   |
| ----------------- | ------------------------ |
| immutable         | record                   |
| no annotations    | avoid framework coupling |
| no business logic | DTO is transport         |

---

# 8. Controller Conventions

## 8.1 Controller Naming

Controller:

```
<Entity>Resource
```

Example

```
AccountResource
```

---

## 8.2 Controller Rules

Controller:

* không business logic
* chỉ delegate use case
* không gọi repository

Bad:

```java
accountRepository.save(...)
```

Good:

```java
createAccountUseCase.execute(request)
```

---

## 8.3 API Path Convention

```
/api/<entities>
```

Examples:

```
/api/accounts
/api/orders
/api/products
```

---

## 8.4 HTTP Method Mapping

| Action  | Method |
| ------- | ------ |
| create  | POST   |
| update  | PATCH  |
| replace | PUT    |
| delete  | DELETE |
| read    | GET    |

Example:

```
POST /api/accounts
PATCH /api/accounts/{id}
```

---

# 9. Database Conventions

## 9.1 Table Naming

Tables:

```
<context>_<entities>
```

Example:

```
iam_accounts
billing_invoices
```

---

## 9.2 Column Naming

Columns dùng:

```
snake_case
```

Example:

```
created_at
updated_at
account_id
```

---

## 9.3 Primary Key

Primary key:

```
id BIGINT
```

External identifier:

```
uuid VARCHAR
```

---

# 10. Exception Handling

## 10.1 Domain Errors Only

Business errors phải dùng:

```
DomainError
```

Example:

```java
AccountError.EMAIL_ALREADY_EXISTS
```

---

## 10.2 Throwing Errors

Throw bằng:

```java
throw AccountError.EMAIL_ALREADY_EXISTS.exception();
```

---

## 10.3 Do Not Throw

Avoid:

```
RuntimeException
IllegalStateException
```

Trong domain logic.

---

# 11. Logging Conventions

## 11.1 Logger in Use Cases

Dùng Lombok `@Slf4j` cho use case. Không khai báo logger thủ công.

Good:

```java
@Slf4j
@RequiredArgsConstructor
public class LoginAccountUseCase implements UseCaseService {
```

Bad:

```java
private static final Logger log = LoggerFactory.getLogger(LoginAccountUseCase.class);
```

---

## 11.2 When to Log

Use logging cho:

* entry/success của use case
* errors và business rule violations (trước khi throw)
* integration events, external calls

Avoid logging:

* domain logic thuần
* internal operations không cần trace

---

## 11.3 Log Levels

| Level  | Dùng cho                                              |
| ------ | ----------------------------------------------------- |
| **INFO**  | Bắt đầu use case (entry), kết thúc thành công (success) |
| **DEBUG** | Chi tiết luồng (verify, parse token, gửi OTP, v.v.)   |
| **WARN**  | Vi phạm nghiệp vụ trước khi throw (invalid credentials, not found, v.v.) |
| **ERROR** | Exception từ integration / external (khi catch rồi rethrow) |

Example:

```java
log.info("Login attempt for email={}", maskEmail(request.email()));
log.debug("Password verified for accountId={}", account.getId());
log.warn("Login failed: invalid password for accountId={}", account.getId());
log.info("Login successful for accountId={}, accountUuid={}", account.getId(), account.getUuid());
```

---

## 11.4 Security

* Không log password, refresh token, access token.
* Mask email khi log (tránh enumeration, ví dụ: `ab***@domain.com`).
* Chỉ log identifier an toàn: `accountId`, `accountUuid`, `sessionId`.

---

# 12. Transaction Conventions

Transaction handled tại repository.

Do NOT use:

```
@Transactional
```

trong:

```
UseCase
Controller
```

---

# 13. Testing Conventions

## 13.1 Test Types

| Test             | Purpose          |
| ---------------- | ---------------- |
| Unit Test        | Domain logic     |
| Repository Test  | Database mapping |
| Integration Test | Full flow        |

---

## 13.2 Naming

```
<Class>Test
```

Example:

```
AccountTest
AccountRepositoryTest
CreateAccountUseCaseTest
```

---

## 13.3 Test Method Naming

Pattern:

```
should<Behavior>When<Condition>
```

Example:

```
shouldActivateAccountWhenStatusPending
```

---

# 14. Performance Conventions

## 14.1 Avoid N+1

Prefer:

```
join queries
batch fetch
```

---

## 14.2 Use Pagination

Never return large collections.

Use:

```
Page
Slice
```

---

## 14.3 Index Strategy

Add index for:

```
uuid
foreign keys
search fields
```

Example:

```
email
status
created_at
```

---

# 15. Code Formatting

Follow standard Java conventions.

Indent:

```
4 spaces
```

Max line length:

```
120 chars
```

---

# 16. Imports

Avoid wildcard imports.

Bad:

```
import java.util.*;
```

Good:

```
import java.util.List;
```

---

# 17. Constants

Constants phải nằm trong:

```
libs/constant
```

Naming:

```
UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
```

Example:

```
DEFAULT_PAGE_SIZE
MAX_RETRY_COUNT
```